
This example sets up three build.jenga files. Here and in the two subdirs.
The rules contained have no cycles, but each build.jenga depends on files
generated by rules in the both other build.jenga files.

Also, the parent build.jenga defines targets in both subdirs.
The reverse does not occur, because we disallow it in jenga.

Currently it is only possible to make a build starting from the parent directory.
Attempting to build starting from either subdirectory causes a build failure.
But this IS behavaiour we wish to support.
